commit_message: Matrix was one too small in both dimensions.  Small bugs in creation of matrices.  Traceback was not doing things right, fixed.
Fixed small glitches causing bad alignments, it still doesn't like huge gaps which current optimal alignment has at beginning
Added a method that uses the Hirschberg algorithm which computes alignments using linear space and only twice the time of dynamic programming.  Not currently outputting correct alignment
Added a submatrix class that can build itself from file and has a better interface.  Test included
Made reading sequence file more generic, returning array of 2 sequences
Initial commit of ported c to java code.  Keep sequences around 500 to avoid running out of memory
